who fell in <name ref="https://mel-catalog.herokuapp.com/api/entries/event:39" type="event">the Assault of Kenesaw Mountain, Georgia</name></hi>

</p><p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">They said that <name ref="https://mel-catalog.herokuapp.com/api/entries/person:260" type="person">Fame</name> her clarion dropped
  Because great deeds were done no more—
That even Duty knew no shining ends,
And Glory—&apos;twas a fallen star!
  But battle can heroes and bards restore.
    Nay, look at Kenesaw:
Perils <name ref="https://mel-catalog.herokuapp.com/api/entries/person:312" type="person">the mailed ones</name> never knew
Are lightly braved by <ref target="#ref_20238">the ragged coats of blue</ref><note xml:id="ref_20238">"The ragged coats of blue" is metonymy for Union troops. </note>,
And gentler hearts are bared to deadlier war.</p></div></body>
